    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-07-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 788/70–76.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Consul-General <persName type="to">Straight</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 31, Consular.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch, No. 72, of May 21, 1907, confirming your cipher telegram of May 20 and
                    transmitting copy of your dispatch, No. 105, to the legation at Peking, with
                    reference to the agreement of the Chinese foreign office to exempt foreign goods
                    from inland taxation within the open cities.</p>
                <p>The department commends you for the ability with which you have thus far
                    conducted your part in this matter.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <p>For the Secretary of State:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Carr</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chief Clerk.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
